title: The Meeting of Eastern and Western Art - From the XVI Century
description:
The Meeting of Eastern and Western Art. From the Sixteenth Century to the Present Day
New York Graphic Society | 1973 | ISBN: 0821205439 | English | 302 pages | PDF | 36.6 MB

The interaction between the art of China and Japan and that of the West, though intermittent and full of misunderstandings, has significantly altered and enlarged the vision of both artists and public in the East, in Europe, and later in America. Michael Sullivan is concerned not with the superficial borrowing of motifs, but with artistic influence at a creative level of awareness of aims and aesthetic ideals. This fascinating strand in the history of art is explored at length in this book for the first time
